===Etymology===
From {{der|en|pt|Florianópolis}}. The city was named after {{w|Floriano Peixoto}}, the second president of {{l|en|Brazil}}, with the addition of the {{l|pt|-polis}} suffix from {{der|en|grc|πόλις||city}}. Before 1893, the city was known as {{l|en|Desterro}}, from the Portuguese word {{l|en|desterro}}, meaning banishment or exile.

